			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There are Bard mobs and NPCs in the game, however none of them use songs because the way EQ is coded every mob in the zone is basically in one big 'group', and so positive songs would affect the entire zone (targetted mob spells, once casting has started, have no line-of-sight or distance restrictions, and group songs are treated as targetted), and pass agro all over the place, not to mention the mess one of the level 20 'mail' Bards would make of the newbie zones buffing the level 1 mobs.
<br />

<br />
So Bard mobs and NPCs are basically just weak Warrior mobs and NPCs. Those few that use Bard-like songs and abilities have them specially coded in.
<br />

<br />
This info is directly from a dev btw, a couple of years back. There was a good reason they couldn't use negative (offensive) songs too, but I'm afraid my memory has failed me on that point.
<br />

<br />
Katawarl</span></td>
